A Lagos High Court sitting in Ikeja has sentenced one Muritala Salami to death for armed robbery. Justice Adenike Coker found Salami guilty of a two-count charge of conspiracy and robbery on Wednesday, March 18, 2020. The prosecuting counsel Jide Martins, a director with the Department of Public Prosecutions (DPP) in Lagos State justice ministry said Salami and his gang conspired and robbed one Okocha Anthony Afiam of two phones and two wristwatches. Justice Coker said the armed robbery gang leader was convicted of conspiracy to commit robbery contrary to section 299 of criminal law and Armed Robbery contrary to section 297 (a) of the Criminal law. Lagos State justice ministryâ€™s spokesman Kayode Oyekanmi in a statement said the convict in April 2016 led a four-man gang to a robbery operation before his arrest. Oyekanmi said other members of the robbery gang escaped during the time of the arrest.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .